name: Mt. Everest
description: Mount Everest is Earth's highest mountain above sea level, located in the Mahalangur Himal sub-range of the Himalayas.

name: Pashupatinath
description: Pashupatinath Temple is a Hindu temple dedicated to Pashupati, and is located in Kathmandu, Nepal. This temple was classified as a World Heritage Site in 1979.

name: Rara Lake
description: Rara Lake is the biggest fresh water lake in the Nepalese Himalayas. n September 2007, it was declared a Ramsar site, covering 1,583 ha including the surrounding wetland.

name: Tea Garden
description: The tea garden of Nepal, is located about 700 km east of Kathmandu. It is famous for natural scenery and landscapes, tea production, and diverse agricultural economy.

name: Phewa Lake
description: Phewa Tal or Fewa Lake is a freshwater lake in Nepal formerly called Baidam Tal located in the south of the Pokhara Valley.
